net_sales_PhoneCases = mergedsales_net[mergedsales_net['category_name'] == 'Phone Cases']
net_product_PhoneCases = product_result[product_result['category_name'] == 'Phone Cases']

import numpy as np

net_FPCsales = net_sales_PhoneCases.price_index.head(500)
weightsa = np.ones_like(net_FPCsales)/float(len(net_FPCsales))
plota = net_FPCsales.hist(weights=weightsa)

net_FPCproduct = net_product_PhoneCases.price_index.head(500)
weightsb = np.ones_like(net_FPCproduct)/float(len(net_FPCproduct))
plotb = net_FPCproduct.hist(weights=weightsa)

# This Graph is aggregation of all product categories

n,x,_ = plt.hist(net_FPCproduct, bins=np.linspace(-1,4.5,25), weights=weightsb)
densityb = stats.gaussian_kde(net_FPCproduct)
n,y,_ = plt.hist(net_FPCsales, bins=np.linspace(-1,4.5,25), weights=weightsa)
densitya = stats.gaussian_kde(net_FPCsales)


plt.suptitle('Total:Net Suppy & Demand of Phone Cases Category', fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel('Net Price Index', fontsize=10)
plt.ylabel('Probability Density', fontsize=10)
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0.)

plt.plot(x,densityb(x))
plt.plot(y,densitya(y))

plot_lines = []
legend1 = pyplot.legend(["Available", "Purchased"], loc=1)
#plt.legend(handles=[plt], loc=4)
pyplot.gca().add_artist(legend1)

plt.show()
